        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": {
            "text": "Improper Mobile Credential Usage (M1): Auth token and username persisted in Android SharedPreferences MODE_PRIVATE without EncryptedSharedPreferences or Android Keystore binding. Attacker recovering a lost, stolen, or rooted device can dump the app's data partition and extract long-lived credentials, achieving full account impersonation without any PIN or biometric challenge.",
            "markdown": "Migrate credential storage to Android Keystore + EncryptedSharedPreferences (Jetpack Security). Bind key release to BiometricPrompt.CryptoObject with StrongBox-backed keys. Rotate session and refresh tokens on every use with server-side revocation. References: OWASP M1:2024; OWASP MASTG-AUTH; CWE-287; CWE-312"
          },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [
