        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
          "message": {
            "text": "Debug Log PII Leakage via Logcat: Debug Log.d(\"auth\", \"user=\" + username + \" token=\" + token) retained in the release build writes authentication material (username and session token) to the device-shared logcat sink accessible to other privileged apps or root shell.",
            "markdown": "Gate all Log.d/Log.v/Log.w calls on BuildConfig.DEBUG via a logging facade (Timber). Replace sensitive-context logs with redacted structured entries. Run a lint rule (LogDetector) in CI to fail the build on unguarded Log.d usage. References: OWASP M8:2024; CWE-532; OWASP MASTG-CODE"
