        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
          "message": {
            "text": "Insecure Mobile Communication (M5) — Client-to-Backend: TLS to WellnessBank Backend API without certificate pinning (no OkHttp CertificatePinner, no Network Security Config pin-set). An attacker on a rogue Wi-Fi access point can MITM the TLS session, intercepting session tokens, transaction payloads, account balances, and PII in transit.",
            "markdown": "Configure OkHttp CertificatePinner with primary + backup pins on all backend hosts. Declare pin-set in network_security_config.xml. Set minimum TLS version to TLS 1.3; reject RC4/3DES. References: OWASP M5:2024; OWASP MASTG-NETWORK; OWASP MASVS-NETWORK; CWE-295"
          },
          "level": "warning",
