          "message": {
            "text": "Backend API Verbose Error Response Exposure: Mobile-backend REST APIs without declared error sanitization may return stack traces, internal service names, database field names, or configuration details in error responses visible to the mobile client.",
            "markdown": "Implement centralized error handling that returns generic error codes to clients; log full error context server-side only. Never serialize internal exceptions or ORM error objects in client-facing responses. References: OWASP A05:2021; CWE-209"
